results.name: Fibonacci(n-J(n,5)) mod n^2, where J is the Jacobi symbol.
comment: a(n) == 0 for n > 1 iff either n is a Wall-Sun-Sun prime (when n is prime) or a 'Wall-Sun-Sun pseudoprime' (when n is composite). The numbers meeting the second criterion are those composites where the congruence in A241505 is satisfied modulo n^2. No members are known from either of those two sets of numbers. - _Felix Fröhlich_, May 15 2015
